article.headline: Dji Bailey makes a go-ahead layup with 13.8 seconds remaining to help Richmond beat Duquesne 63-61
article.description: — Neal Quinn scored 16 points, Dji Bailey made a go-ahead layup with 13.8 seconds remaining and Richmond knocked off Duquesne 63-61 on Tuesday night for its seventh straight victory.

article.story: PITTSBURGH -- — Neal Quinn scored 16 points, Dji Bailey made a go-ahead layup with 13.8 seconds remaining and Richmond knocked off Duquesne 63-61 on Tuesday night for its seventh straight victory. Quinn had eight rebounds for the Spiders (12-5, 4-0 Atlantic 10 Conference). Bailey added 12 points while going 4 of 5 from the field, and he also had eight rebounds. Jason Roche shot 3 for 7, including 3 for 5 from beyond the arc to finish with 11 points. The Dukes (9-7, 0-4) were led in scoring by Jimmy Clark III, who finished with 16 points and four assists. David Dixon added 12 points and six rebounds for Duquesne. Fousseyni Drame also put up eight points and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
